{% block bodyContent %}

<p>NHS England has a licence for 3 weights of the Frutiger font, which is the brand font for the NHS. Monotype owns the font.</p>
<p>NHS organisations in England can register to use the font for free under a "sub-licence". You must sign up to these terms to get a sub-licence.</p>
<p>You do not need to register if your team is part of NHS England.</p>
<h2>The fonts covered by the sub-licence</h2>
<p>NHS England's licence covers Frutiger in 3 weights:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Frutiger 65 Bold</li>
  <li>Frutiger 55 Roman</li>
  <li>Frutiger 45 Light, but you cannot use this in an app</li>
</ul>
<p>You must buy your own licence if you want to use:</p>
<ul>
  <li>any other font or font weight, such as Frutiger Italic</li>
  <li>Frutiger 45 Light in a mobile downloadable NHS app</li>
  <li>Frutiger in a way that is not covered in the sub-licence</li>
</ul>
<p>The sub-licence covers the font version that NHS England bought in December 2024. It does not cover later versions.</p>

<h2>What you can and cannot do with a sub-licence</h2>
<p>You must:</p>
<ul>
  <li>manage access to the font and only let people in your organisation or your suppliers use it</li>
  <li>make sure that people using the font agree to these terms</li>
</ul>
<p>You are responsible for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>your users' and suppliers' use of the fonts and compliance with your sub-licence</li>
    <li>any unauthorised access to the font and font software on your or their systems</li>
    <li>any claims by Monotype for your, your users' and your suppliers' misuse of the font or font software</li>
  </ul>
<p>You must not sub-licence the font to another organisation or give anyone outside your organisation access to it, with the exception of suppliers.</p>
<p>NHS England is not responsible for any losses, claims or liabilities arising our of your, your users' or suppliers' use of the font or font software on your or their systems.</p>
<p>You cannot use Monotype's font platform or its app to get these free fonts. You can only get them by registering here in the NHS digital service manual.</p>
<h3>Suppliers</h3>
<p>You can give suppliers access to the font to produce NHS branded goods or services for you.</p>
<p>You must make sure that they:</p>
<ul>
  <li>agree to these terms</li>
  <li>delete any font files you have given them at the end of the job</li>
</ul>
<h3>The font files</h3>
<p>You must not:</p>
<ul>
  <li>change the font or its software or use it to make other fonts</li>
  <li>embed the font software code in open source software in a way that makes it publicly available</li>
  <li>extract or use the font metadata</li>
  <li>transfer or user the font or font software outside the UK</li>
</ul>

<h3>Using the font in different products, systems and services</h3>
<details class="nhsuk-details">
