    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="nhsuk-details__text">
    <p>You can install the software on servers that you control or servers that a third party controls for you.</p>
    <p>You can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>use the font to create, edit and distribute documents or other materials</li>
      <li>embed it into electronic documents (but not in digital marketing communications - see below)</li>
      <li>back it up internally</li>
      <li>for digital informational content (?)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You must make sure that materials you create:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>do not contain the font software or allow any part of it to be extracted</li>
      <li>only have images of the font that cannot be edited</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If you use the font, font software or materials in a collaborative cloud environment, you can let users view and edit the document but not otherwise use the font.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<details class="nhsuk-details">
  <summary class="nhsuk-details__summary">
    <span class="nhsuk-details__summary-text">
      Digital marketing communications
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="nhsuk-details__text">
    <p>You can embed the font and font software into digital marketing communications and use the font in editable documents, like Word.</p>
    <p>You must make sure your content does not allow people to download, reformat or reuse the font code.</p> 
  </div>
</details>

<details class="nhsuk-details">
  <summary class="nhsuk-details__summary">
    <span class="nhsuk-details__summary-text">
      Print and other physical items
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="nhsuk-details__text">
    <p>You can use the font and font software to create, edit, print, and produce printed and other physical items.</p>
  </div>
</details>
             
<details class="nhsuk-details">
  <summary class="nhsuk-details__summary">
    <span class="nhsuk-details__summary-text">
      Logos and marks
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="nhsuk-details__text">
    <p>You can use the font and font software in any logos or marks.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<h2>Issues or claims</h2>
<p>The font and font software are provided on an "as is" basis.</p>
<p>If you have any issues with the fonts or font software covered by this sub-licence, contact X at NHS England. Do not contact Monotype. You cannot make a claim against Monotype directly.</p>

<h2>Breaches of the sub-licence</h2>
<p>You must let us know immediately if you breach your sub-licence.</p>
<p>You must fix any breaches you can within 60 days.</p>
<p>NHS England or Monotype can end your sub-licence and rights to use the font if you breach it.</p>
<p>If Monotype makes a claim about your, your users' or your suppliers' use of the font, you must help us and give us any reasonable information we ask for. This may include providing a list of font users and details of how you use the font.</p> 

